li.p: OIDC Provider (in AWS IAM): This lets your GitHub Actions securely connect to AWS by allowing it to temporarily assume an IAM Role.
IAM Role: Create a dedicated IAM Role for GitHub Actions. This role must have the necessary permissions to manage your infrastructure, including resources in S3, DynamoDB, and CloudFront.
S3 Bucket for Statefile: You'll need an S3 bucket to store your Terraform state file. Make sure you enable versioning on this bucket for easy rollbacks.
